<h1>Privacy Policy – Parser</h1>

<p>At <strong>FOUAD ELKHADIRI NETWORK LLC</strong>, we respect your privacy and are committed to protecting any information you share with us. This Privacy Policy explains how our mobile application <strong>Parser</strong> collects, uses, and safeguards your data.</p>

<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

<p>Depending on how you use Parser, we may collect:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Anonymous interaction data such as pages viewed, features accessed, and time spent inside the app.</li>
    <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Device model, operating system version, app version, and general technical details to improve compatibility and performance.</li>
    <li><strong>Crash Logs & Performance Data:</strong> Automatically collected to detect crashes, errors, and performance issues.</li>
</ul>

<p>We do not collect personal information such as your name, address, phone number, or precise location unless you voluntarily provide it (for example, when contacting support).</p>

<h2>2. How We Use the Information</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Improve app stability and functionality</li>
    <li>Diagnose and resolve crashes or technical issues</li>
    <li>Enhance the overall user experience</li>
</ul>

<p>We do not sell, rent, or share your data with unrelated third parties.</p>

<h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
<p>Parser may use trusted third-party services including:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Google Play Services</li>
    <li>Firebase Analytics / Crashlytics</li>
    <li>AppLovin MAX (advertising and monetization)</li>
</ul>
<p>These services may collect data as described in their own privacy policies.</p>

<h2>4. Advertising</h2>
<p>Parser may display ads provided by <strong>AppLovin MAX</strong>.
AppLovin may use cookies or similar technologies for personalized or contextual advertising.</p>

<p><strong>Opt-out:</strong> Android &gt; Settings &gt; Google &gt; Ads &gt; Opt-out of Ads Personalization.</p>

<h2>5. Data Security</h2>
<p>We take reasonable measures to safeguard collected data, but no system is 100% secure.</p>

<h2>6. Children’s Privacy</h2>
<p>Parser is not intended for children under 13. If data from a child under 13 is found, it will be deleted immediately.</p>

<h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Continued use of Parser after changes means you accept the updated terms.</p>

<h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
<p>If you have any questions or concerns:</p>
